page.title: 01Nature Reserve in Cree Wood
page.content: The Valley of the River Cree runs along the East side of the block. A steep rise takes the Wood out to open moorland which covers about two thirds of the area. Cree Wood is a bird reservation maintained by the Royal Society for the Preservation of Birds. This old deciduous wood contains mainly Oaks, Ash and Birch, densely covered, heavy with lichen, but clear of undergrowth. It has been well cropped and managed for many years. Few timbers exceed 80cm circumference. There is major growth from stumps. Sparsely populated farming community.
